edu.umd.cs.psl.reasoner.bool

Class BooleanMaxWalkSat

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umd.cs.psl.application.groundkernelstore.MemoryGroundKernelStore
      • edu.umd.cs.psl.reasoner.bool.BooleanMaxWalkSat
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GroundKernelStore, Reasoner

    public class BooleanMaxWalkSat
extends MemoryGroundKernelStore
implements Reasoner
    Implementation of MaxWalkSat, which searches for a good Boolean assignment of truth values.

    See "A General Stochastic Approach to Solving Problems with Hard and Soft Constraints," in The Satisfiability Problem: Theory and Applications (1997), pp. 573-586 by Henry Kautz, Bart Selman, Yueyen Jiang.

    Supports free RandomVariableAtoms and RandomVariableAtoms that are each constrained by a single GroundDomainRangeConstraint.

    It also assumes that all ObservedAtoms have values in {0.0, 1.0}. Its behavior is not defined otherwise.
